  "prompt": "Can an officer in the Indian army get married before 25? What are the circumstances where it might be allowed?",
  "response": "In the Indian Army, officers typically cannot get married before the age of 25. However, there are some circumstances where exceptions can be made:\n\n1. Specific Circumstances for Early Marriage:\n- If the officer receives special permission from the Army Headquarters\n- In case of arranged marriages within the officer's community or family\n- If the marriage is deemed essential due to specific personal or family reasons\n\n2. Conditions for Possible Early Marriage:\n- Detailed written application explaining the compelling reasons\n- Recommendation from the commanding officer\n- Character verification and background check\n- Obtaining formal approval from higher military authorities\n\n3. Potential Scenarios:\n- Medical reasons\n- Cultural or traditional family obligations\n- Exceptional personal circumstances\n- Strategic family alliances\n\n4. General Requirements:\n- Must submit a comprehensive application\n- Demonstrate that the marriage will not negatively impact military service\n- Provide all necessary documentation\n- Undergo a thorough review process\n\n5. Process:\n- Application goes through multiple levels of military hierarchy\n- Final decision rests with Army Headquarters\n- Each case is evaluated individually\n\nWhile exceptions exist, the general policy discourages early marriages to ensure officers are professionally and personally stable before matrimony.",
